last_episode_to_air.name: Puppification
last_episode_to_air.overview: At an appliance store, Michael blends juices with a sticker. Then, at a pet shop, he reverses the food chain. Plus, at a doggy spa, an old dog learns new tricks when a rejuvenation machine turns back time and Michael doesn't go unscathed.

name: The Carbonaro Effect
overview: Michael Carbonaro is a magician by trade, but a prankster by heart. Michael performs baffling tricks on unsuspecting people in everyday situations, all caught on hidden camera. Everyone is left stunned and delighted, even though they have no idea what just hit them.

episodes.name: Got the Bug Out
episodes.overview: Posing as a technician, Michael literally "gets the bug out" of a customer's phone and has him convinced it was in there all along.

episodes.name: A Problem with Chocolate Turtles and Seeds
episodes.overview: Posing as a cashier, Michael makes a shopper's face appear on a milk carton and tries to convince her that she really is a missing person. Then, in a shipping store he has customers believing that impossible technology of the future has arrived, like a bowling ball that can be mailed in a flat box. Plus, he has a hotel guest questioning her identity when he swaps her ID, and stumps a valet when he does a disappearing act from his car.

episodes.name: A Waddle, a Scratch...
episodes.overview: A duck fools thrift store shoppers; an endless chain of hangers; cheese corks in a liquor store; freezing wine; destroying and reconstructing art in a museum.

episodes.name: Just Smash It Out
episodes.overview: Michael convinces car wash patrons that he broke their window, only to miraculously fix it with the push of a button. Then, dry cleaning customers are confused when Michael is suddenly wearing their clothes in the blink of an eye. Plus, pet shoppers see fish in a dry water bowl.

episodes.name: Out of Bounce
episodes.overview: Too good to be true toys; Michael poses as a personal trainer who sweats a bucket-full; a disappearing car makes a security guard panic.

episodes.name: Don't Freeze Me
episodes.overview: A light box turns heavy in a sporting goods store; Michael poses as a barista for a glass illusion; a boomerang in a museum; taxidermy mischief.

episodes.name: The Lizard Law
episodes.overview: A lucky serpent at a Mexican restaurant; metal-melting salsa; a brown bag lunch that keeps on giving; the freshest frozen entrée ever; dead flowers revived.

episodes.name: It's a Makeshift
episodes.overview: Never ending laundry soap; a human phonograph at the thrift store; a flipping punch bowl; a teleporting glass penguin.

episodes.name: Green Friendly
episodes.overview: A shrinking wine bottle with a confounding cork; vanishing diamonds in a jewelry store; going green at the car wash.

episodes.name: Maybe it's the Echinacea?
episodes.overview: Posing as a Pet Store employee, Michael sells customers on the novelty of pets that can hatch out of balloons and convinces a hotel valet that he can park a car without even sitting in the driver's seat.

episodes.name: Serious Déjà Vu
episodes.overview: Posing as a bartender, Michael turns water into liquor and convinces a self-proclaimed experienced drinker that distillation is a lie.

episodes.name: An Elevated Ferret Alert
episodes.overview: At a car wash, Michael uses a unique method to retrieve keys that were locked in a car, and horrifies a woman who does not want new furry friends.

episodes.name: Cause and Effect
episodes.overview: In this special episode, Michael breaks the laws of physics with a multitude of tricks and then introduces new technologies to some very accepting patrons.

episodes.name: This is Not an Orange
episodes.overview: Michael confuses variety store customers with products that have secret hideaways; astonishes camping store patrons with rafts that come in pill form; and convinces a woman that a tiny propeller enables human levitation.

episodes.name: Just During the Previews
episodes.overview: Michael tests gravity when he floats the idea of astronaut snacks; his darkness-triggering popcorn and he astonishes an antique store employee with glass figurines that feel emotion and repair themselves.

episodes.name: In Case What?!
episodes.overview: Michael stumps a delivery man when he pulls live crabs out of his Chinese food order.

episodes.name: A Faux Pas to Wear
episodes.overview: Michael stuns shoppers with a remarkably advanced antique that self-tailors clothes and a chalkboard that solves mathematical equations.

episodes.name: Just a Milker
episodes.overview: Michael fishes for trouble in a toy store with pop-up books that contain live animals and, at a health food store, he shows a woman how to milk almonds; a mummy causes an employee to question ancient curses.

episodes.name: Suburban Pimp
episodes.overview: Michael gets spooky at an antique store with a vintage voodoo doll and, at a costume store, a Dorothy outfit comes complete with a little dog too.

episodes.name: Might Be Trippin'
episodes.overview: Michael fills in for a karate instructor and interrupts the Zen of his students; a frog necklace that is so realistic; a clothing display that puts the "man" in mannequin.

episodes.name: An Awogami Is Ripe
episodes.overview: Michael works at a camping store where his life-saving s'mores and pop-up coolers stun customers; a child safety pill bottle with built-in invisibility proves too complicated for adults; Michael adjusts the size of a model train.

episodes.name: Iguanasaurs
episodes.overview: Michael shrinks into a leprechaun outfit; a museum employee makes the discovery of a lifetime when a preserved egg hatches a baby dinosaur.

episodes.name: 3D Galastical Morphin Ranging Power Tents
episodes.overview: Michael tries to pull a fast one on burger joint patrons with his inflatable hot dogs and his unusual technique for bagging buns, then he creeps out a flea market vendor when he brings an acrylic encased arachnid back to life.

episodes.name: Flash Melt
episodes.overview: Michael hits the jackpot in a convenience store with a man who guesses the winning lotto numbers and amazes a mother at a toy store when he demonstrates her own child's genius abilities.

episodes.name: An Over-grooming Situation
episodes.overview: Michael leaves a co-worker with a technologically confounding hose that wirelessly transmits water; Michael's puppy takes to the catwalk after dressing himself in the most fashionable canine attire.

episodes.name: Just Made History
episodes.overview: In the season two premiere, Michael poses as a hipster at a farmers market and makes an endless supply of juice. Then things become blurry at the eye doctor, and later, shape shifting aliens send Michael's co-worker into a frenzy.

episodes.name: Dangerously Drinkable
episodes.overview: Michael astounds dental patients with molar radio transmissions, and while appraising art, he brings an extinct species back to life. Plus, an unusual brew stirs a ghostly hallucination that will make draws drop.

episodes.name: Japanese Waterless Folding Toilet
episodes.overview: Michael stretches headphone cords and reality with a mystical putty and stuns a co-worker with new bathroom technology. In the big finale, a Porta Potty becomes a Portal Potty.

episodes.name: The Albino Corn Snake Viper Patrol
episodes.overview: Working at a tattoo parlor, Michael gets some killer ink in a flash. Then it's SNAKES ON A SEDAN when a serpent ambushes a routine car checkup. Down on the docks, one unlucky guy learns a lesson in shrinkage.

episodes.name: Amvox 73
episodes.overview: Michael unearths a mutant turtle from a mystical Peruvian clay. A woman is blown away when 2 adorable bunnies become 8 and to top it off, a hapless carpenter becomes an accidental time traveler when a potent new glue has him coming undone.

episodes.name: Turn to Gold
episodes.overview: A miraculous liquid gives Michael the Midas touch in an eyeglass store. Later, Michael trains the new girl at a tanning salon, but things take horrifying turn when she believes she's killed her first customer.

episodes.name: Take the Mirror
episodes.overview: Michael's candy shop customers witness a live scorpion get freed from a lollipop and later Michael's cocktail invention has one man drunk with envy! In the big finish, a cursed mirror turns simple reflections into reality.

episodes.name: Sierra Volcano
episodes.overview: Michael performs a revolutionary treatment that turns back time and at the farmer's market, a pungent pre-historic  cheese mesmerizes one shopper's taste buds. Plus, an accident with a 3D printer has Michael meeting his match.

episodes.name: The Doughy Parts
episodes.overview: At an office, Michael goes from suave to slacker in the blink of an eye. Then at a museum, a man discovers his painter's touch is worth thousands and at a pool club, Michael and his strange friend are in the deep end with security.

episodes.name: That's Voodoo
episodes.overview: Michael wows mall shoppers with snakes that sooth and spiders that stitch. At an art supply store a woman finds out that she's a natural born wood whittler. Plus, an abandoned house won't let go of its precious things.

episodes.name: Catch the Flu
episodes.overview: Michael helps a man realize his amazing mind powers and an art gallery's tribal mask goes missing which has the security guard fearing war.

episodes.name: Deep Space Air
episodes.overview: While doing scientific research, Michael makes things heavy with some otherworldly air. At  a bakery, the new rolls are so light that they defy gravity. Michael then gets caught by the ultimate sand trap as a golf instructor.

episodes.name: Fishguise
episodes.overview: At a local copy shop, Michael introduces a print by hand technique and at a bait and tackle shop, he unveils the latest fish fashion trends. At an office, Michael pulls a switcheroo and the new temp has no idea who's the boss.

episodes.name: EggShaq
episodes.overview: Michael unveils the mystery behind bowling balls, and does the world's longest spit take; Shaquille O'Neal helps with a plan to blow one super-fan's mind.

episodes.name: Dead Man Walking
episodes.overview: Michael serenades a clam while posing as a cook; a spirited trick leaves one man questioning the afterlife.

episodes.name: I Am Ogle Thorpe
episodes.overview: When Michael opens a shocking package at a warehouse, a man goes hog wild. And while pigs may not fly, Michael proves that kittens can. One woman believes a curse has transformed a man right before her eyes.

episodes.name: The Framing Canon
episodes.overview: While working in an art supply store, Michael astounds a customer with a framing device, shocks a patron who can't see the whole picture and becomes a piece of art. Later, a woman goes haywire when Michael literally loses his head.

episodes.name: Skull with a Flower Hat
episodes.overview: While posing as a security guard, Michael turns a metal detector into a microwave, exposes a surveillance operation and finds himself in the line of fire. Later, a mover is dumbfounded when a woman rises from the ashes.

episodes.name: Warthogs, WogHearts and Hogwarts
episodes.overview: Michael refreshes stale nachos and peels back the truth behind a fake bill. He also unveils the latest in cellular soda machine technology. But what will happen when he breathes life into a T-Rex?

episodes.name: A Positive Presence
episodes.overview: Michael serves a drink that can eat away at anything and cleanse so organic that it creates life. Later, his sneaker lacing technology shocks a customer and makes an assistant think someone has risen from the dead.

episodes.name: Top Priority of NASA
episodes.overview: Michael's tricks include a soup fit for space, odd ear wax removal and a mystic massage. Later, a mover travels through time.

episodes.name: Drone Care
episodes.overview: While working as a florist, Michael nukes petal popping flowers, sheds light on frog mutation, and turns an ant farm into a work of art.

episodes.name: Sets Itself, Lights Itself
episodes.overview: Michael loses a credit card in a series of absorbing containers. In an art store, he shakes off sloppy handwriting to reveal some fancy calligraphy. Later on, a catering assistant gets spooked when the chinaware sets itself.

episodes.name: A Living Trilobite
episodes.overview: Michael proves chipmunks are nature's accountants; Michael stuns a museum worker by bringing a fossilized creature to life.

episodes.name: House of Horrors
episodes.overview: Michael unveils a coffee making app and gets textually active with the world's thinnest disposable phone. Then he debuts a new beauty invention that turns ugly.

episodes.name: He's a Professional Dude
episodes.overview: Michael silences a traveling squeak while remodeling a home; a hospital becomes the scene of a mind-bending game of cops and robbers.

episodes.name: Incredibly Unsettling
episodes.overview: Michael breezes into the Windy City to shock and amaze the Chicago locals. In a health store, he sells a supplement that proves you are what you drink, and at a Metro station, he utterly derails a commuter's sense of reality.

episodes.name: Holy Moly Mirror
episodes.overview: In a local Chicago diner, Michael brings new meaning to the term "hold the pickles". Plus, he discovers an aggressive new breed of fungus at a park, and later, he helps a co-worker disappear from work early in a hospital warehouse.

episodes.name: Bro, They're Surrounding Us!
episodes.overview: At a market, Michael reveals an amazing credit card hack, and at a science shop, he demonstrates how far stem cell research has come. Later, Michael spooks a gardener who's certain that angry gnomes are hunting him down!

episodes.name: It's a Chicken, Sir!
episodes.overview: Discovering a ferocious new breed of animal at a park; invading a local tea shop; Michael transforms himself at an abandoned art studio.

episodes.name: Wait, My Chair!
episodes.overview: Michael shows a caterer the true power of dairy products, and an antique store customer is stunned when a species of termite chews through the scenery.

episodes.name: Soliciting Statue
episodes.overview: Michael shows off an impossible way to organize your clothes; there are some surprises lurking in our favorite foods at the super market; Michael pushes his skills by tricking two people at the same time.

episodes.name: Speed Thieves
episodes.overview: At a diner, Michael adds some spice to lunchtime and gives patrons the chills while demonstrating a new way to cool soup. And at a furniture store, Michael shows his coworker that impossible things can happen in the blink of an eye.

episodes.name: The Impractically Carbonaro Jokers' Effect
episodes.overview: In this special crossover event, the Impractical Jokers help Michael stun coffee bar customers - but soon discover the joke is on them; on a nature trail, Michael's woodland creatures display fantastic hidden abilities.

episodes.name: A Similar Rock Energy
episodes.overview: Michael is back in Chicago to hash out new ideas in a hemp store, but it's not until he inspects a spooky church that people start getting stoned, literally. Plus, Michael teams up with special guest star, Jack Black!

episodes.name: Kind of Like a Seafoam Green
episodes.overview: Michael shows some unsuspecting shoppers how to manipulate solid objects, and he reveals the truth about automatic vacuums; one employee's shift at a camping store becomes very colorful and confusing.

episodes.name: Super Saturn Moon Travel
episodes.overview: At Michael's fireworks stand, he's got everything from exploding fruit to levitation sparklers, and at a hemp store, Michael shows off his innovations in hemp technology. Plus, a time capsule completely blows one man's mind!

episodes.name: Cuban Assimilatory Persea Plant
episodes.overview: Michael tries new foods like shape-shifting pasta and never-ending soup! Then it's off to a vinyl shop for a record-breaking illusion, and later, Michael tries to convince his coworker to explore a new plant.

episodes.name: Pixelated Vision
episodes.overview: At a wilderness store, Michael reels in customers with an amazing new fishing tool, and at an AT&T store, Michael shows off a camera that's literally paper thin. Plus, a day of mini golf turns explosive when a loose cannon appears.

episodes.name: Italian Food Matter
episodes.overview: Michael uncovers the secrets behind baoding balls, origami and paper lamps, and at Eataly, he reveals a spray that turns everything into bacon. Plus, a picture worth a thousand words leaves Michael's assistant speechless.

episodes.name: Industrial Asphalt Sealant
episodes.overview: Michael trains his coworkers how to hold a dog who can't hold it, and at the AT&T store, Michael shows off a new way to lighten the load. Plus, a man can vanish into a manhole, but the whole hole can't vanish, right?!

episodes.name: Pineapple Breeze
episodes.overview: At a cell phone store, Michael reveals an exciting new way to fix your tablet, and later, he makes a drink that's impossible to swallow. Plus, a dog owner loves that Michael has turned her pet into the smartest animal in the world!

episodes.name: Total Face Rejuvenation
episodes.overview: Michael shocks a receptionist with a medical procedure that leaves both their jaws on the floor.

episodes.name: Relax the Back
episodes.overview: Michael shocks people with every trick in the book at a library, including a voice-controlled page turner.

episodes.name: The Snowball
episodes.overview: Michael visits a ski shop to demonstrate the latest in winter gear; a hat that also makes hot cocoa.

episodes.name: You’ve Been Marked
episodes.overview: Michael shows off a seashell from the seashore, that still has the seashore in it.

episodes.name: Simon Soft
episodes.overview: Michael turns iced tea into a tea candle.

episodes.name: Whippit
episodes.overview: In an ice cream shop, Michael whips up a mind-boggling app.

episodes.name: The Food Flattener
episodes.overview: At a cooking class, Michael gets crabby when chopping salad and brings the heat to instantly cook a meatball with his breath.

episodes.name: Dr. Bones
episodes.overview: Michael explores the true depth of a deep-dish pizza.

episodes.name: There's Life in Here
episodes.overview: Michael gives a confused woman the license to speed at the Department of Motor Vehicles.

episodes.name: Prehistoric Fossil Breeding
episodes.overview: Michael schools a man on fish fossil breeding at a rock store.

episodes.name: Vegan Plant
episodes.overview: Michael feeds a cannibalistic plant at a garden center.

episodes.name: Sorcery or Science
episodes.overview: Michael sweetens a woman's day at a candy store when a chocolate bunny eats here ring.

episodes.name: Fight or Flight
episodes.overview: While working at a cheese store, Michael milks the reaction of a woman stunned by breeding brie.

episodes.name: Fright at the Museum
episodes.overview: At a campsite, Michael turns rain into wine and has an app that gives a new meaning to the "call of nature."

episodes.name: Dummy Talks
episodes.overview: At an appliance store, a man goes bananas over Michael's self stocking fridge.

episodes.name: Home Run Away
episodes.overview: At a deli, Michael bakes bread with power tools, and in a tux store, his outfit change doesn't suit his customer.

episodes.name: Cat Lady
episodes.overview: At auditions, Michael wows directors with costume changes but cracks when he sings; things get sticky when he demos flying post-its; Michael's co-worker's jaw drops when a shape-shifting tenant returns while they clean house.

episodes.name: Moving Dragon
episodes.overview: While working at a pool store, Michael flies on a kickboard and shows the culinary uses of a pool noodle; at a pet store, he breeds hamsters from pellets; Michael stuns his helper as moving day heats up with a fiery statue.

episodes.name: Lipstick and the Flying Nun
episodes.overview: While working at an antique shop, Michael unpacks an item with a message from beyond and a problem-solving toy puzzles his co-worker. Plus, Michael works a fundraiser where a painting raises not just money but the body of a nun.

episodes.name: Pink Slime
episodes.overview: While working at a book store, Michael feeds some book worms. Plus, Michael serves food and gives new meaning to the term "grass fed beef". Then, at a food testing center, Michael spooks his assistant when an experiment takes a new shape.

episodes.name: Chilly Flakes and Wormholes
episodes.overview: Michael works in a spice shop and gets the icy treatment with his take on "chilly flakes". Plus at a hotel, he cleans a spill with his phone. And then, at an abandoned house, Michael amazes his assistant when he climbs through a wormhole.

episodes.name: Popcorn Pants
episodes.overview: Michael delivers a shock in a shipping store when packaged wine tips over and gets the bubble wrap tipsy. At a popcorn shop, Michael dons the latest kernel fashions. Later, at a theater, he stuns his helper when a trick jumps off the screen.

episodes.name: Vanishing Daycare
episodes.overview: At a thrift store, Michael transforms a t-shirt that's suitable for all four seasons and at a daycare, his aid thinks she loses more than her mind. Plus, in a museum, Michael's helper runs scared when a sculpture starts to slither away.

episodes.name: Puppification
episodes.overview: At an appliance store, Michael blends juices with a sticker. Then, at a pet shop, he reverses the food chain. Plus, at a doggy spa, an old dog learns new tricks when a rejuvenation machine turns back time and Michael doesn't go unscathed.
